SIMPLE: undated
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undated
<hw>Un"da*ted</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n"d⟦asl⟧*t⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>undatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>undare</ets> to rise in
waves, to wave, to undulate, fr. <ets>unda</ets> a wave. See
<er>Undulate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Rising and falling in
waves toward the margin, as a leaf; waved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undated</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Undated
<hw>Un*dat"ed</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*d⟦amac⟧t"⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>dated</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not
dated; having no date; of unknown age; <as>as, an <ex>undated</ex>
letter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undauntable</ent>⟦br⟧
